						<summary>

						<p>On the South wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Brahmapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Kulōttuṅgachōḷadēva, year 17: 1194-95 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of <hi rend="italic">dēvadana</hi> lands at Puravarāinallūr for lamps to the deity Tiruvayaṉīśuram-uḍaiya-nāyaṉār of Vaḻugūr in Irumbēḍu-nāḍu in Jayaṅgoṇḍaśoḻa-maṇḍalam by the <hi rend="italic">nyāyattār</hi> including <hi rend="italic">Kuṟuśēkaṟa</hi> Kaḷappāḷa Sāvakanāyaṉ Ammaiappasāvakan.</p>						

						</summary>
